originalText.text:
Wonderful little spot with affordable delicious small plates during happy hour. When you walk in there is a nice bar and small tables for people to sit. They have a small outdoor patio area that they open on nice days.

We came as a party of 2 and got the shredded chicken nachos, the guacamole and the empanadas. The guacamole is delicious. They left some whole ingredients on top instead of chopping them up but it worked out nice. The shredded chicken nachos are probably the best thing that we got and were quite delicious I highly recommend them. The empanadas tasted more like a samosa that came with a mint green chutney.

The happy hour menu also had a lot of drink specials. I would come here again during happy hour.

originalText.text: The waitress was really pleasant and accommodating, and the service was quite nice. She gave us a thorough breakdown of the menu and gave us her recommendations. I have to admit that all of her recommendations for food, beverages, and overall quality were well received. The food was also perfectly seasoned. I have no complaints given the pricing. Despite not being a big drinker, I had to get more drinks since they were so excellent.

originalText.text: As a native Southern Californian, it's difficult for me to find legit Mexican food in other states. Anejo comes close to the variety, quality and taste I would expect from a great Mexican Food restaurant. We tried the pineapple guacamole, the pork belly tacos and octopus with the Pork Belly tostados coming in for the win. The next time we're in town, we'll try additional items and hit the cocktail menu!
